## USER RESEARCH

### Top 5 Pain Points
1. **Opacity uncertainty**: Users struggle knowing how many coats achieve "the right amount" of translucency—too sheer looks unfinished, too opaque loses jelly effect
2. **Streak prevention anxiety**: Thin jelly polish shows every application flaw; users worry about streaky, uneven coverage visible through translucency
3. **DIY mixing confusion**: When mixing clear + colored polish at home, ratios are guesswork—results vary wildly, waste polish trying to perfect formula
4. **Appropriate occasion doubt**: Unsure if sheer nails are "too casual" for romantic Valentine dates vs safe for work/everyday wear
5. **Embellishment integration**: Difficulty adding Valentine details (hearts, glitter) to sheer base without disrupting translucency or looking muddy

### User Sentiment
Intrigued yet cautious—users love the aesthetic but fear execution difficulty; seeking permission that "barely there" nails can be Valentine-appropriate and romantic (not lazy or unfinished-looking)

